5:
Ooh, that shop over there looks
interesting too!
14:
You guys sure bought a lot... Let me
carry some of that for you!
18: Really? Thank you so much, Alk!
21: All right, on to the next one!
34:
Sorry, Alk... You purposely took the
heavy things off our hands, right?
38:
Hey, no problem. This much I can
handle.
41:
You're as strong as a horse! Hmm,
how much more do you think you
could carry? Just checking. How
about double what we have now?
44:
D-double?! I'm not ACTUALLY a
horse, you know.
48:
It's just that there are so many
interesting things on this world! You
say that most of it sank into the
water?
53:
Yes. Items that get salvaged from
the water tend to go for a very high
price.
56:
So you have to pay a premium price
for older items, huh? I get it, but I
personally prefer new stuff.
60:
I can definitely see that, judging by
your outfit!
65:
I'm glad you noticed! This is the
latest outfit from Code Lilian!
Striking, isn't it?
68:
Oh, and it's not just my clothes. My
magic is brand-new as well!
Sometimes I even make up new
spells from scratch.
71:
You create new spells? Wow, that's
seriously impressive.
75:
Older magic tends to be very...
inefficient. There's always room for
improvement.
78:
When I make enough progress in
my magic research, I try to update
my spells!
86: Well, I guess I do give it my best?
89:
That's the thing about being a mage
though... You're always surrounded
by old stuff.
91:
Mostly old traditions that you have
to respect. "That's how it's been
done, so that's how we're gonna do
it!" That type of thing.
98:
Not necessarily... But I think it's
definitely lagging behind with the
times.
101:
I think we need a more modern
approach to magic, you know?
105:
Yes. The way you use magic is very
cool, Façon.
109:
To be fair, it's not like I do away with
the old entirely.
112:
Sorry, could you wait here a
moment?
120:
I've never seen magic like that. It has
such an odd composition...
123: Oh, don't worry. I'm a mage as well!
126:
Heed me, spirits of water. Manifest
yourselves before me!
129:
Wow! Y-you can use magic too,
miss?
133:
That's right.
Say... Where did you even learn how
to do this?
138:
You mean... You figured out how to
do this all on your own?! That's
incredible.
144:
Um, it's just... I can't get this one to
work right!
148:
I want to split this orb into two, but I
don't know how...
154:
Er, you know what, never mind. Here,
I'll show you how to do it!
161:
W-wow! That was awesome! I
actually did it!
165:
It's not like I came up with this spell!
That's actually a super old one.
170:
Could you teach me more
awesome magic again, Miss?
173:
Sure. Just let me know when you
need some help, and I'll pop on by.
177:
To that girl, it didn't matter at all
whether the magic was old or new...
Huh.
181:
Nice job, Façon. You looked like you
had a fun time.
185:
Say, Alk. Is there a place nearby
where we can see all those
salvaged items you were talking
about?
188:
Uh, yeah, I think so! There should be
a few shops over in that direction.
193:
I'm feeling curious all of a sudden,
so I think I'll go make the rounds, if
you don't mind.
